{{Location map-line|lat=-80}} [[Image:Antarctica Map.png|thumb|]] The '''80th parallel south''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 80 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[south]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]].
It passes through [[Antarctica]] and Antarctic [[ice shelf|ice shelves]].
==Around the world== Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 80° south passes through:
