[[File:Sogn og Fjordane våpen.svg|thumb|right|Coat of arms of Sogn og Fjordane county]] The '''coat of arms of Sogn og Fjordane''' is an official symbol of [[Sogn og Fjordane]] county, [[Norway]].<ref>[https://snl.no/kommunev%C3%A5pen/fastsettelse_av_kommunev%C3%A5pen ''kommunevåpen – fastsettelse av kommunevåpen'' (Store norske leksikon, 2005 - 2007)]</ref>
The [[coat of arms]] features the geographical layout of the county. The three blue peaks on a silver background symbolize the three fjords of the county: [[Nordfjorden (Sogn og Fjordane)|Nordfjord]], [[Sunnfjord]], and [[Sognefjord]]. The name of the county is derived from these fjords. Nearly all villages, towns and population centers are situated on one of these fjords.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ngw.nl/int/nor/sognfjord.htm|title=Sogn og Fjordane|publisher=Norske Kommunevåpen|accessdate=23 August 2008}}</ref>
The coat of arms was introduced on 23 September 1983. It is almost exclusively used by the [[Sogn og Fjordane County Municipality|County Administration]] and use by others must be approved by them in advance. A banner of the coat of arms is used as the [[Flag of Sogn og Fjordane|county flag]].
