{{Expand Russian|История почты и почтовых марок Люксембурга|date=February 2015}} [[File:Luxembourg1923scott151-B1-B4.jpg|thumb|1923 Stamps of Luxembourg]] [[File:1883 Luxembourg telegraph stamp 25c.jpg|thumb|An 1883 25c [[telegraph stamp]] of Luxembourg]] This is a survey of the '''[[postage stamps]] and [[postal history]] of [[Luxembourg]]'''.
Luxembourg is a landlocked country in western Europe, bordered by Belgium, France, and Germany. Luxembourg has a population of over half a million people in an area of approximately 2,586 square kilometres (999 sq mi).
== First stamps == Luxembourg issued its first stamps on 15 September 1852. The stamps were issued in both Belgian and Prussian currency but later issues were issued only in Belgian currency.<ref name=ross>[[Stuart Rossiter|Rossiter, Stuart]] & John Flower. ''The Stamp Atlas''. London: Macdonald, 1986, p. 60. {{ISBN|0-356-10862-7}}</ref>
